If you wondering how to listen for whether a user has pressed down or up on a particular key on their computer keyboard, first Google how to do this. It's a common query and you'll quickly find many answers (some of them offering overly-complicated solutions, so focus on the more straightforward ones). 

If you're still stuck after that, scroll down to line 50 for another hint!














































You can add onKeyUp and onKeyDown to the "main" container div to listen for these events. Within the event object that gets passed into your event handler, you can then determine the key that has gone down or up by looking at the event's "key" property. 